"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.1.12\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.1.12</span> 標題：灌溉水渠、運河（irrigation channel, canal）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： יְאֹר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： y’or)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:19\">EXO 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:1\">EXO 8:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： נָהָר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： nahar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:6\">ISA 19:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： διῶρυξ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： diōrux)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir24:30\">SIR 24:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir24:31\">SIR 24:31</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ὑδραγωγός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： udragōgos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir24:30\">SIR 24:30</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0333_irrigation_channel.jpg\" alt=\"從瓦迪凱爾特（Wadi Kelt）到耶利哥的灌溉管道\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">從瓦迪凱爾特（Wadi Kelt）到耶利哥的灌溉管道 (© Bukvoed, CC BY 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>灌溉水渠是在岩石上鑿出來或者在地上挖出來的小水道，把水從河流等較大的水源引到種植莊稼的田地裡面。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir24:30\">SIR 24:30</a> 描述了灌溉水渠的作用：「我如從河裡引出來的水道，我如通到樂園的水渠」（《思》）。在澆灌園子時，把水從較大的水渠引到若干條較小的水渠，然後送到園子的各處；這個系統利用重力來輸送水。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>希伯來文<em>y’or</em> 通常指的是尼羅河。但是，大多數譯本都同意這個詞在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:19\">EXO 7:19</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:1\">EXO 8:1</a> （《和》8:5）中是指「灌溉用運河」。同樣，希伯來文<em>nahar</em> 通常表示「一條河」，但這個詞在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:6\">ISA 19:6</a> 的希伯來文本中為複數，大多數譯本將這個詞譯為「運河」（“canals”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> ）或「渠道」（“channels”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> ）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
